instance virtual_to_physical_interaction : DTDFVocab:VirtualToPhysical [
    base:desc "The DT sends desired speed, ACC enable/disable flags, emergency braking commands, and steering corrections back to the PT through ROS 2 services/topics; these are consumed by the Actuation FE on the Jetson Orin Nano, which drives the motor voltage and steering servo actuators, and triggers the braking subsystem."
]

instance twinning_time_scale : DTDFVocab:TimeScale [
    base:desc "Real‑time vehicle state is sampled at the perception cycle (typical 30–60 Hz); end‑to‑end communication latency from vehicle to DT must not exceed 100 ms, and all clocks are synchronised to within 100 ms (as specified in R7 and R8)."
]

instance dt_constellation : DTDFVocab:Constellation [
    base:desc "The DT constellation follows the ISO 23247 entity architecture: Observable Manufacturing Element analogue (Physical Twin), Digital Twin Entity, User Entity, each consisting of a set of Functional Entities (Data Translation, Data Collection, Presentation, Reporting, Controlling, Actuation). Communication flows over ROS 2 topics/services within the DT and over Wi‑Fi between PT and DT, with Data Translation serving as the cross‑system glue."
]

instance life_cycle_stages : DTDFVocab:EvolutionStage [
    base:desc "The DT operates in the ‘Operated’ phase of the vehicle lifecycle, providing real‑time monitoring and remote control after manufacturing; it also supports design validation via simulation during development, but the case study focuses on operational use."
]

instance fidelity_and_validity_considerations : DTDFVocab:FidelityConsideration [
    base:desc "Fidelity is achieved through high‑fidelity sensor data processing (DBSCAN, Kalman filter), real‑time latency constraints (≤100 ms), clock synchronisation (≤100 ms accuracy), and compliance with ISO 15622 control logic. Validation involves comparing real‑time vehicle state against DT reports, ensuring that AC commands produced by the DT match expected behavior under varying lead vehicle distances."
]

instance dt_technical_connection : DTDFVocab:TechnicalConnection [
    base:desc "Inter‑entity communication uses ROS 2 DDS over Wi‑Fi; within the DT, ROS 2 nodes communicate via DDS topics; between PT and DT, data is transmitted over UDP/TCP (ROS 2 transport) over a Wi‑Fi network, with a dedicated Data Translation FE handling serialization."
]

instance dt_hosting_deployment : DTDFVocab:Deployment [
    base:desc "The PT runs the Physical Twin Entity on an NVIDIA Jetson Orin Nano; the Digital Twin Entity and User Entity are hosted on a local workstation or cloud edge node (not explicitly specified) and are packaged as ROS 2 containers or executables. The system is orchestrated via ROS 2 launch files that spin up each entity on its respective hardware."
]

instance standardization : DTDFVocab:Standardization [
    base:desc "ISO 23247 Part 2 (Reference Architecture) is the primary guideline; ISO 15622 defines ACC control logic; ROS 2 follows DDS communication standard; OPC UA mentioned but not used. All software follows open‑source licensing under the project repository."
]
